    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>07</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2026-06-03</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Reported to House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2026-06-17T22:46:50Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>SBA Artificial Intelligence Utilization Act of 2026</strong></p><p>This bill requires the Small Business Administration (SBA) to annually report on the SBA's&nbsp;use of artificial intelligence and machine learning.</p><p>The report must include information about&nbsp;(1) the benefits and risks posed by the SBA's use of artificial intelligence and machine learning; and (2)&nbsp;measures that the SBA can take to identify, evaluate, and manage such benefits and risks, including explanations of how the SBA can retain human involvement in decisions informed by the&nbsp;use of artificial intelligence or machine learning.</p><p>Additionally, not later than 30 days after submitting each report, the SBA must brief the&nbsp;House Committee on Small Business and the Senate Committee on Small Business and Entrepreneurship about the report.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
